<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 14:52:47 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>摘要：通讯地址：Koji Haratani，Department of Medical Oncology, Kindai University Facilities of Medicine, 377–2 Ohno-higashi, Osaka-Sayama, Osaka 589-8511, Japan</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/abstract-address-correspondence-to-koji-haratani-department-of-medical-oncology-kindai-university-faculty-of-medicine-377-2-ohno-higashi-osaka-sayama-osaka-589-8511-japan</link><description>电话：81.72.366.0221；电子邮件：&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/abstract143.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 14:52:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/abstract-address-correspondence-to-koji-haratani-department-of-medical-oncology-kindai-university-faculty-of-medicine-377-2-ohno-higashi-osaka-sayama-osaka-589-8511-japan</guid></item><item><title>阅读短头颅狗的面部表情需要人类进行额外的认知处理</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/reading-brachycephalic-dogs-facial-expressions-requires-extra-cognitive-processing-by-humans</link><description>人们经常通过观察狗的行为，尤其是它们的面部表情，来了解它们的心理状态。大量研究表明这是一种流行的解释策略。然而，现代狗品种的大小和结构差异很大，很少有研究探讨品种特定的形态如何影响人类评估不同品种狗的面部视觉线索的能力。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/reading-brachycephalic-dogs-facial-expressions-requires-extra-cognitive-processing-by-humans.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 14:37:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/reading-brachycephalic-dogs-facial-expressions-requires-extra-cognitive-processing-by-humans</guid></item><item><title>一项新的测试可以通过拍摄眼球来标记有贫血风险的人——无需针头</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-new-test-could-flag-people-at-risk-for-anemia-by-filming-their-eyeballs-no-needles-required</link><description>一种新的无针技术尚未准备好取代抽血，但它可以作为一种筛查工具来标记需要全面血液测试的人。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-new-test-could-flag-people-at-risk-for-anemia-by-filming-their-eyeballs-no-needles-required.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 14:22:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-new-test-could-flag-people-at-risk-for-anemia-by-filming-their-eyeballs-no-needles-required</guid></item><item><title>更准确地预测带隙能量</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-more-accurate-prediction-of-band-gap-energies</link><description>温度是半导体带隙能量的调节旋钮，而半导体带隙能量又在光电器件的性能中发挥着关键作用。但是，根据第一原理预测这种温度依赖性的计算工具很难捕捉一个主要因素的影响：电子-声子相互作用中的多电子效应。加州大学伯克利分校的龚晓迅及其同事现在展示了一个计算框架，可以正确解释这些影响[&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-more-accurate-prediction-of-band-gap-energies3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 14:07:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-more-accurate-prediction-of-band-gap-energies</guid></item><item><title>双梳光谱如何工作以及为什么它可以重塑精密传感</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-dual-comb-spectroscopy-works-and-why-it-could-reshape-precision-sensing</link><description>光谱学有许多应用，从量子电动力学的基本测试和分子结构的研究到环境传感、生物医学诊断和工业监测。多年来，出现了一种有潜力改变该领域的非常有前途的光谱仪器：双梳光谱仪，它依赖于两个锁模超快激光器的干涉，产生由均匀间隔的窄光谱线组成的宽频率梳。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-dual-comb-spectroscopy-works-and-why-it-could-reshape-precision-sensing2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 13:52:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/how-dual-comb-spectroscopy-works-and-why-it-could-reshape-precision-sensing</guid></item><item><title>隐藏的大脑回路可以解释运动错误如何提高新技能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/hidden-brain-circuit-could-explain-how-movement-errors-sharpen-new-skills</link><description>虽然人类正在学习需要进行协调运动的新技能，例如步行、演奏乐器或滑板，但众所周知，随着时间的推移，他们的大脑会不断发现错误并纠正动作。这种对特定任务运动的逐渐习得被称为运动学习。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/hidden-brain-circuit-could-explain-how-movement-errors-sharpen-new-skills.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 13:37:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/hidden-brain-circuit-could-explain-how-movement-errors-sharpen-new-skills</guid></item><item><title>水星的水冰可能是由比之前想象的更大、更慢的撞击器沉积的——仅在一天之内</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mercurys-water-ice-may-have-been-deposited-by-a-larger-slower-impactor-than-previously-thought-in-only-one-day</link><description>隐藏在水星极地地区的大量水冰沉积物的来源一直是研究人员争论的话题。一项新研究， &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/mercurys-water-ice-may-have-been-deposited-by-a-larger-slower-impactor-than-previously-thought-in-only-one-day3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 13:22:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/mercurys-water-ice-may-have-been-deposited-by-a-larger-slower-impactor-than-previously-thought-in-only-one-day</guid></item><item><title>低功耗、灵活的射频晶体管突破 100 GHz 障碍</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/low-power-flexible-radio-frequency-transistors-break-100-ghz-barrier</link><description>在过去的几十年里，世界各地的电子工程师一直在努力开发能够实现设备之间更快通信、同时消耗更少能源的设备。为了满足第六代 (6G) 无线通信技术的要求，这些设备应在 100 吉赫兹 (GHz) 以上的频率下运行。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/low-power-flexible-radio-frequency-transistors-break-100-ghz-barrier3.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 13:07:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/low-power-flexible-radio-frequency-transistors-break-100-ghz-barrier</guid></item><item><title>TESS 发现三重食三星系统</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/triply-eclipsing-triple-star-system-discovered-with-tess</link><description>天文学家利用美国宇航局的凌日系外行星勘测卫星（TESS）发现了一个三重食恒星系统。这个新发现的系统被命名为TIC 295741342，由食双星中的两颗类太阳恒星和围绕双星运行的巨大第三伴星组成。 5 月 19 日在 arXiv 预印本服务器上发表的一篇论文报道了这一发现。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/triply-eclipsing-triple-star-system-discovered-with-tess.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 12:52:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/triply-eclipsing-triple-star-system-discovered-with-tess</guid></item><item><title>天体物理学家利用引力波探测宝库挖掘黑金</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/astrophysicists-strike-black-gold-with-treasure-trove-of-gravitational-wave-detections</link><description>格拉斯哥大学引力研究所的研究人员正在庆祝引力波探测的巨大新宝库的出版，被誉为标志着引力天文学时代到来的里程碑。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/astrophysicists-strike-black-gold-with-treasure-trove-of-gravitational-wave-detections2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 27 May 2026 12:37:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/astrophysicists-strike-black-gold-with-treasure-trove-of-gravitational-wave-detections</guid></item></channel></rss>